    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">What SEER rating is recommended for Arkansas?</h3>
    <p>For Arkansas's hot, humid climate, HVAC systems with SEER ratings of 16-20 are recommended for optimal efficiency and comfort. The minimum SEER requirement is 14, but higher ratings provide significant energy savings during the state's long cooling season. Systems with SEER 16-18 offer the best value for most homeowners, balancing efficiency with reasonable upfront costs. Premium systems with SEER 20+ ratings are worthwhile for larger homes or homeowners prioritizing maximum efficiency. Variable-speed systems often provide better humidity control than single-stage units, which is particularly important in Arkansas's humid climate. Heat pumps should have HSPF ratings of 8.5 or higher for efficient winter heating.</p>
